docs.abstract: When it’s a quick trip from the schlocky pleasures of Cancún to the remote cities of the Maya, is something lost along the way?
docs.snippet: When it’s a quick trip from the schlocky pleasures of Cancún to the remote cities of the Maya, is something lost along the way?
docs.lead_paragraph: El Tren Maya, which links five states in southern Mexico, is one of the country’s most-debated infrastructure projects. Carved through the Yucatán Peninsula at great expense, the 966-mile loop pits the megaproject ambitions of Mexico’s departing president, Andrés Manuel López Obrador, against the will of environmentalists and Indigenous leaders seeking to preserve a pristine environment of jaguars, ancient ruins and sacred underwater caves.

headline.main: A New Train Is Opening Up the Yucatán, for Better or Worse
headline.print_headline: All Aboard, For Better or Worse

byline.original: By Matthew Pillsbury and Nicholas Casey

docs.abstract: ‘Elsbeth’ takes a boilerplate police procedural and tosses in a character from another show entirely — with delightful results.
docs.snippet: ‘Elsbeth’ takes a boilerplate police procedural and tosses in a character from another show entirely — with delightful results.
docs.lead_paragraph: The most-watched streaming series of 2023, it turns out, was “Suits.” All your faves — the conceptually and emotionally difficult ones, the family-trauma dramedies, the zombie soaps and franchise space operas — were as dust in comparison with a bouncy basic-cable legal procedural. If Gen Z viewers are looking at the buffet of TV content and choosing old-school blue-sky procedurals over “Succession” or “The Mandalorian,” what becomes of the world all these streamers and premium-cable networks worked so hard to build?

headline.main: Who Is This Strange Woman, and What Is She Doing Here?

docs.abstract: Temperatures in the region rose above 40 degrees Celsius in February, with humidity pushing the heat index even higher.
docs.snippet: Temperatures in the region rose above 40 degrees Celsius in February, with humidity pushing the heat index even higher.
docs.lead_paragraph: A remarkably early, record-breaking heat wave hit the southern part of West Africa in mid-February. Climate change made this extreme heat 10 times as likely, according to a new analysis by an international team of scientists. It also pushed the heat index about four degrees Celsius higher than it would have been without the extra greenhouse gases in the atmosphere from burning fossil fuels.

headline.main: Climate Change Made an Early Heat Wave in West Africa 10 Times as Likely

docs.abstract: Many U.S. homeowners are staying put rather than selling, even if they’d prefer to move. These days, renovating may be a better bet.
docs.snippet: Many U.S. homeowners are staying put rather than selling, even if they’d prefer to move. These days, renovating may be a better bet.
docs.lead_paragraph: If you bought a home before mortgage rates shot up to their current levels, congratulations — you’re probably paying much less each month than you would if you moved today and borrowed again. That’s why so many homeowners are staying put, even if they’d prefer to move.

headline.main: Can’t Move? Renovate, if You Can Afford It.

docs.abstract: Naminapu Maymuru-White and Daniel Boyd grew up hundreds of miles and a generation apart. Yet they share a goal: reframing the way we see the universe.
docs.snippet: Naminapu Maymuru-White and Daniel Boyd grew up hundreds of miles and a generation apart. Yet they share a goal: reframing the way we see the universe.
docs.lead_paragraph: At Art Basel Hong Kong, two celebrated First Nations Australian artists will present complex and contrasting perspectives on Indigenous identities. In their work, the two artists, Naminapu Maymuru-White and Daniel Boyd, carry on a long tradition of creative expression — harnessing and exploring the history of the hundreds of distinct peoples who established homelands across Australia more than 50,000 years ago.

headline.main: Two Aboriginal Artists Urge Viewers to See the Universe Differently
headline.print_headline: From a different point of view
